cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection using deep convolutional neural networks and unsupervised saliency. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper deals with image analysis and object detection. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image segmentation, which is a sub-field of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
